                    conversationalText = "Airway fire is an operating room emergency. Announce fire, immediately stop oxygen and nitrous oxide flow, remove the endotracheal tube, extinguish the airway with saline/water, ventilate with room air or an alternative gas source, then reassess oxygen need. Perform bronchoscopy to evaluate injury and debris. Reintubation, ICU care, and monitoring for airway edema/burn injury may be required. The team and equipment should be reviewed afterward.",
