                    conversationalText = "In Fontan physiology, systemic venous blood (from IVC/SVC) is directed into the pulmonary arteries without a ventricular pump. Pulmonary blood flow depends entirely on a passive pressure gradient between systemic venous and left atrial pressure. Maintaining low pulmonary vascular resistance (PVR) and adequate preload (systemic venous return) is critical. Avoid hypoxia, hypercapnia, acidosis, high airway pressures, and high PEEP. Preserve sinus rhythm and correct hypovolemia immediately.",
